02/06/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A two-day meeting of the political bureau of the European People's Party (EPP) opened Thursday (2 June) in Bucharest, the first such session to be held in Romania.
The 47 representatives of the EPP in the European Parliament are attending.
EPP parliamentary caucus leader Hans Gert Poettering told local media that the party is open to political parties from Romania that have similar party platforms.
(Rompres, Cotidianul - 02/06/05)
